<p style='margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;font-size:15px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;margin-top:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;line-height:107%;margin:0cm;'><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:#0E101A;'>The world is not only polluted by big oil companies or coal mines, but the fast-growing fashion industry is also to blame that is responsible for the poor living conditions of the farmers and the low mineral quality of the soil due to the extensive use of chemicals. Thankfully, this trend is changing for the good.</span></p>
<img class="mt-3" src="../assets/images/eco-friendly-cloth1.jpg" alt="sports" style="width:100%; object-fit:cover;">

<p style='margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;font-size:15px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;margin-top:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;line-height:107%;margin:0cm;text-align:center;'><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:#0E101A;'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p style='margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;font-size:15px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;margin-top:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;line-height:107%;margin:0cm;'><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:#0E101A;'>As of 2021, the nitty-gritty consumer behaviour patterns indicate that the future for commerce and retail markets are speeding through roads where the final destination will be a town named as sustainability with organic pesticide-free raw materials and creative reuse of nature&apos;s gifts as its inhabitants.</span></p>
<p style='margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;font-size:15px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;margin-top:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;line-height:107%;margin:0cm;text-align:center;'><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:#0E101A;'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p style='margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;font-size:15px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;margin-top:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;line-height:107%;margin:0cm;'><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:#0E101A;'>Since the advent of 2017, clothing items manufactures have used the keywords like &quot;Recycled,&quot; &quot;Climate-Friendly,&quot; &quot;Green,&quot; and &quot;Eco&quot; in a more massive amount than they used to in the past in markets like the United States and the United Kingdom and some other parts of the world. These amounts of buzzwords were said to have an increase of 125 percent. Also, one can see that the ecological products have seen an uprise of 49 percent, and those termed as recycled have rocketed with a 173 percent increase.&nbsp;</span></p>
<img class="mt-3" src="../assets/images/eco-friendly-cloth2.jpg" alt="sports" style="width:100%; object-fit:cover;">

<p style='margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;font-size:15px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;margin-top:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;line-height:107%;margin:0cm;'><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:#0E101A;'>&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style='margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;font-size:15px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;margin-top:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;line-height:107%;margin:0cm;'><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:#0E101A;'>Did you know that according to a report study done in 2021, 53% of consumers would prefer green products, and nearly 75% are willing to shell out more amounts for environmentally friendly clothing?</span></p>
<p style='margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;font-size:15px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;margin-top:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;line-height:107%;margin:0cm;text-align:center;'><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:#0E101A;'>&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style='margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;font-size:15px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;margin-top:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;line-height:107%;margin:0cm;'><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:#0E101A;'>Raising the question of what fabrics could save the future and help the environment? Well, there are a few, namely, Newlife, a type of polyester yarn (made from 100% recycled plastic bottles that would otherwise end up in landfills), Lyocell branded as Tencel is a cellulose fibre (prepared from dissolving pulp), Industrial Hemp products cause zero damage to the environment (a species of the Cannabis Sativa plant) and many more.</span></p>
<p style='margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;font-size:15px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;margin-top:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;line-height:107%;margin:0cm;'><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:#0E101A;'>&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style='margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;font-size:15px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;margin-top:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;line-height:107%;margin:0cm;'><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:#0E101A;'>The founders of the Adiff fashion industry Angela Luna and Al-Saad, are stating the fact of buying these products rather than just embracing them. They also reported that due to the high prices, many people are not able to bill these green fashion items.&nbsp;</span></p>
<img class="mt-3" src="../assets/images/eco-friendly-cloth3.jpg" alt="sports" style="width:100%; object-fit:cover;">

<p style='margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;font-size:15px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;margin-top:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;line-height:107%;margin:0cm;'><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:#0E101A;'>&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style='margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;font-size:15px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;margin-top:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;line-height:107%;margin:0cm;'><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:#0E101A;'>The whole process of eco-friendly products is not as simple as it might sound. Firstly, there has to be a transformative change and massive funding of $20 billion, but the excellent news sits as the world&apos;s preference in terms of clothing fabric is shifting; thereby, the funding is now much more accessible. The Vogue Business interlocutors studied the future of fashion in terms of sustainability and how to promote better practices for the fashion industries, mainly focused on start-ups.</span></p>
<p style='margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;font-size:15px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;margin-top:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;line-height:107%;margin:0cm;'><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:#0E101A;'>&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style='margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;font-size:15px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;margin-top:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;line-height:107%;margin:0cm;'><span style='font-family:"Arial Black",sans-serif;color:#0E101A;'>Definition of environmentally friendly clothing line: -</span></p>
<p style='margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;font-size:15px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;margin-top:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;line-height:107%;margin:0cm;'><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:#0E101A;'>&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style='margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;font-size:15px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;margin-top:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;line-height:107%;margin:0cm;'><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:#0E101A;'>The products under this category seek out in terms of their impact on the environment. Phrased differently, one can say, how can the fashion manufacturers produce, purchase, sell and design apparels that have a minimalistic effect on nature during their production and after they are discarded? Also, keeping in mind the packing materials used, as most of these materials are thrown away instantly.</span></p>
<p style='margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;font-size:15px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;margin-top:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;line-height:107%;margin:0cm;text-align:center;'><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:#0E101A;'>&nbsp;</span></p>
